<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-08T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-08T12:00:00-05:00" n="903" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d903">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.1124 Bitzer, John Andre/6:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-08T17:00:00+00:00">November 8, 1939—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2690. Your 1313, October 26, 6 p.m. Foreign Office upon Embassy’s
                                request has taken up the John Andre Bitzer case with the authorities
                                at Beirut and is awaiting a reply.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>